headline: The overlooked issue of domestic violence against elderly women
description: Among all women killed by their partners in France in 2024, 26% were over the age of 70, a figure that is on the rise. Yet, the murders of these women and the possible abuse that preceded them are poorly documented.

headline: Previously unknown Renoir painting sells for €1.8 million at auction
description: The oil painting by French impressionist painter August Renoir of his toddler son Jean had never before been exhibited or sold. The high-end art market has been experiencing a recent boon, with record-breaking sales in the past week alone for works by Frida Kahlo and Gustav Klimt.

headline: Boualem Sansal: 'At my age, I am not about to learn to hold my tongue...'
description: The French-Algerian writer, who has been in France since November 18, has regained his freedom, including his freedom of speech. He recounts his yearlong detention in Algeria, discusses the remarks that led to his arrest, and reflects on the future of relations between France and Algeria.
